reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works as expected but isn’t new.
reviews.reviewText: Price was great and it works with no problems. It’s obviously not new though. Cooler was new or at least appeared to be new.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This chip is solidly worth $130+. I purchased this for a small home server. The performance is really exceptional given what you get. This part is originally OEM only so none of the chips are 100% 'new' but they have gone through multiple QA processes. The Wraith cooler I received had a defective fan. I can't hold that against CUK, that happens. I ordered a way more amazing cooler which wasn't a problem for me at all. I'm sure CUK would have replaced it if I would have asked.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Okay product, terrible customer support
reviews.reviewText: I spent about two weeks troubleshooting this product, trying to identify why there were debug lights on my motherboard. I reached out to the vendor day 1 based on a business card included in the packaging. I received no response.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little budget chip
reviews.reviewText: It has a full compliment of PCIe lanes, unlike its Zen and Zen2 based predecessors. No more worrying about what will have lanes where.Due to the vastly reduced L3 cache in this Zen3 Cezanne APU (8MB vs the usual 32MB), this chip ends up having about the same IPC as a Zen2 chip. I have it installed in my travel / testing rig, and it is more than capable of keeping me gaming on the go. Could also be the heart of a DIY NAS, or an office productivity system.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not 'New,' but works well
reviews.reviewText: The processor was definitely not 'New,' but, it works, and came with the original accessories. I suspect that Computer Upgrade King (the seller) pulls these from systems they upgrade before reselling them, so, the processor was potentially unused, but, I do wish this was more clear in the listing - the price is good, the product is genuine, there isn't really a good reason not to disclose that this is (most likely) a reclaimed OEM part, especially if it's unused.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exclent igpu for your buck. So what if it is used.
reviews.reviewText: Used it as a mediacenter pc ....... Works great and no problems. Used Win 11 as well

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good performance to price. This was an OEM only CPU, but it worked for me.
reviews.reviewText: This CPU is surprisingly power efficient for its era, and comes at a very good price right now. Be aware, it was an OEM only item originally, and my Asrock MoBo did not list it as compatible, but ASUS and MSI did, and it worked for me in my Asrock B450 mother board. You get 4 cores and 8 threads (as compared to 8/16 for the 5700, but it can be less than 1/2 the price, so you can get into this CPU for about $80 right now. a 4/8 core/thread 4100 without the graphics is only $10 cheaper. The video output did not work with the motherboard I was using, but I have not updated the drivers yet, and everything else is working and I am using a GPU anyways.
